{
  "stem": "7556.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So in the evening, when we were already in bed, [INAUDIBLE] they used to come and stay for a few minutes and then leave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, they see each other at work first of all, and after work, we were permitted to walk in the center of the camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So then husbands and wives and boyfriends and girlfriends were together, walking.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was permitted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We heard only that the Russians are coming closer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is what we were-- not told, but you know, the little information form a newspaper or from a radio that somebody had hiding, we knew that the Russians are coming closer.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is when he decided to move the camp to Sudeten.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in Auschwitz also, because women had to go through Auschwitz and men through Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was three weeks in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even the--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think there were 2,000.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know exactly. 200 women, I know, went through Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How many men, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we smuggled some children, and we smuggled some of the women.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They marched us to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A few weeks.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly how many, but I'm sure it was more than three weeks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from there, we went to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were told that we are going to Brinnlitz, to Schindler, but the train made a mistake and we wound up in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] This is the unforgettable sight, the chimneys with the fire and the smell of burned bodies.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we went to the barrack, and maybe the second or the third night, one of the Polish-- OK.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
